        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): add top-level subsystem logger",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds `src/agents/log.ts` exporting a `SubsystemLogger` for the `\"agents\"` subsystem\n- Follows the existing pattern of `src/agents/cli-runner/log.ts` and `src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/logger.ts`\n- Wires `agent-command.ts` as the first caller via `agentsLog.child(\"agent-command\")` — identical runtime behavior to the previous `createSubsystemLogger(\"agents/agent-command\")` call\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `src/agents/log.ts` adds a shared subsystem logger for the agents module so consumers can call `log.child(...)` instead of importing `createSubsystemLogger` directly.\n\nReal environment tested: Node v24.15.0, tsx v4.22.3, openclaw repo on commit e8416d4a36 (Windows 11 / PowerShell)\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```\nnode_modules/.bin/tsx --eval \"\nimport { log } from './src/agents/log.ts';\nconsole.log('subsystem:', log.subsystem);\nconst child = log.child('agent-command');\nconsole.log('child subsystem:', child.subsystem);\nconsole.log('isEnabled(info):', log.isEnabled('info'));\n\"\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\nsubsystem: agents\nchild subsystem: agents/agent-command\nisEnabled(info): true\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: `log.subsystem` is `\"agents\"`, `log.child(\"agent-command\").subsystem` is `\"agents/agent-command\"` — same string the previous direct `createSubsystemLogger(\"agents/agent-command\")` call produced. No behavior change.\n\nWhat was not tested: Other callers that may eventually import from `src/agents/log.ts`; no existing tests changed.\n\n## Verification\n\nCI run on head `e8416d4a36`: `build-artifacts` ✅ `check-dependencies` ✅ `check-prod-types` ✅ `checks-node-agentic-agents` ✅",
